description:
This is a 14 minute workout called '10 minute Lower Body Workout // Floor Exercises for Legs & Glutes' from the channel SeniorShape Fitness.
The workout falls under Cardio/Mat and Flexibility/Pilates.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Foundation Builder and The Comfort Moves vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: This pilates based mat workout will make your legs burn and shake (in the best way) while shaping and toning your lower half.  These moves are all performed on the mat and are challenging but achievable! Want more of a challenge? Add ankle weights! Please go at your own pace and take breaks if you need to. Always start slow, and this workout will get easier every time you do it. Don't give up!
Ooops! I realize this video is 14 minutes and not 10! I may have gotten carried away. Well, that's just more muscle shaping exercises for you!

Exercises will be performed in different body positions. Such as; supported on our elbows, side lying, and on our elbows and knees. If you are uncomfortable on your knees (last glute section) you can also perform these exercises in a standing position slightly hinged forward.

Want more? Check out other 10 minute workouts to mix and match such as arms, cardio, abs and stretching. 10 minute workout playlist here: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLdAl5SsV...
